instance_desc:
The Loan Approval AI System considers nine attributes of the loan application when making a decision. The attribute titles are in the top row of the above table, while the values from this application are in the bottom row.

The loan application can be described as follows. the requested loan amount is 5000; purpose category for the loan request is Major purchase; monthly payment owed if the loan approved is 166.03; annual interest rate is 11.98; number of monthly payments is 36; self-reported annual income of the loan applicant is 70100; their home ownership status is Own; payment received to-date is 5170.53; and interest received to-date is 170.54. All monetary values are in US dollars.
ai_model_result_desc: The Loan Approval AI System is indicating a 99% likelihood of this loan application being Accepted. This suggests a strong possibility that the loan will be approved, based on the provided information. Nevertheless, there remains a very small probability, approximately 1%, that the application could potentially receive rejection.
lime_desc:
This explanation is generated by the LIME explanation technique. There are three key component in this explanation.

The left-most figure displays the possible decisions of the AI system and likelihood of each decision. For this loan application, the AI system is predicting Accepted with a 99% likelihood and Rejected with a 1% likelihood.

The central bar chart shows attribute importance. Each horizontal bar corresponds to a loan application attribute. The bar colours align with possible deicions on the left-most figure. Each bar colour and magnitude indicate the decision it influenced and by how much. The bars are ordered from the most influenced to least influenced attribute. In this loan application, loan amount, monthly installment, home ownership status and interest to-date attribute values contributed the most to the Accepted decision. Payment to-date has contributed to the 1% likelihood of rejected.

The right-most table presents the decisions the AI system would make if only one attribute was considered from the application. This figure further validates the insights from the central figure, where the most influencial attributes on their own are loan amount, monthly installment and home ownership status. Note that the numerical attribute values converted to 0-1 range by the algorithm.

Note that the attribute names are abbriviated by the algorithm. total_pymnt: Payment to-date; loan_amnt: Loan amount; total_rec_int: Interest to-date; term: No of monthly payments; annual_inc: Annual income of the applicant; int_rate: Annual interest rate
shap_desc:
This explanation is generated by the Kernel SHAP explanation technique. It depicts the attribute importance as a bar chart.

The two colours refer to two possible decisions and each bar colour indicates the decision influenced by the attribute value. The length/value within the bar indicates the magnitude of the influence. Bars are ordered by their magnitude of influence on the decision.

In this loan application, loan amount, monthly installment and payment to-date attributes were the most influential to the system decision of Accepted. Starting point of 0.484 on the x-axis on the graph refers to the AI system decision probability when none of the attributes are considered. The top-most point on the plot represents the sum of all contributions, which is equal to the AI system prediction for this loan application (in this case -0.01 is equivalent to 0.99).

Note that the attribute names are abbriviated by the algorithm. total_pymnt: Payment to-date; loan_amnt: Loan amount; total_rec_int: Interest to-date; term: No of monthly payments; annual_inc: Annual income of the applicant; int_rate: Annual interest rate
perf_desc:
This explanation describes the performance of the AI system.

The AI system accuracy is 99.05%. Accuracy quantifies system performance as the percentage of correct predictions.This means the system is likely to correctly predict the decision for 99 out of 100 applications.

The F1-score of the AI system is 98.9% which is very close to system accuracy. This means it not only gets things right but also avoids making unnecessary false positives and false negatives. In other words, the system is both accurate and consistent across different loan application scenarios.

discern_desc:
This explanation is generated by the DisCERN Counterfactual explanation technique. The second row of the table presents the loan application that received a Accepted decision and the third row presents a counterfactual loan application which is similar but with an Rejected decision. Note that the last column indicate the AI system decision for each application.

The counterfactual loan application is highlighting changes that will influence the AI system decision towards a Rejected application. In this case, the two loan applications are similar in the loan amount, loan purpose, number of payments and home ownership status. It is highlighting following attribute changes:

  • Increased monthly installment from 166.03 to 172.33
  • Increased interest rate from 11.98 to 12.65
  • Decreased annual income from 70100.00 to 70000.00

Additionally, there are differences in payment to-date and interest to-date that are likely to affect the AI system decision.
